@ijuma 
thanks a lot for your comment;
It make sense to use 'PROJECT_NAMES';
I made some fix, please take a look when you have time;

@ewencp 
the previous patch doesn't make sense, I modified it;
take a look at the code;
KafkaConsumer will try to do another fetch after every poll, from my understanding, poll(0) will return immediately with any records already available in Fetcher's memory;
If there is chance the message of "task config commit" is consumed twice, logic of consumedCallback in KafkaConfigStorage can be disturbed;

@ewencp 
Hi, It's great to have your comment : )
I agree with you and removed the OFFSET_STORAGE_CLASS_CONFIG config;
please take a look at this when you have time : )

@ijuma I have made the suggested changes...review it and let me know if any further changes would be needed.

Thanks

Praveen
